	<p style="padding: 0px 24px; text-indent:2em;">
	I am currently a student at USC set to graduate in the spring of 2022. I am studying Computer Science: Games, and I am primarily interested in game play engineering and AI. 
	In terms of experience, I have competence and practice in game development in C++ and C#, as reflected in my projects. Outside of game development I am proficient in Java, although I have not used it in games development.
	AS far as experience with common systems in games, I have implemented A* pathfinding both in C++ and in Unity using C#, and I have familiarity with techniques such as, AABB collision, leading edge detection, and ray casting, among others.
	</p>
	
